   <h1>Re: [KG] Kelley Park Rant. (fwd)</h1>
   <b>Thom Fitzpatrick &lt;thom_at_calweb_dot_com&gt;</b><br/>
   <i>2000-04-10 19:00:18+00</i><br/>
   <br/>
   <pre>[...]

From Richard Troy on the KG list

As an aside, one of the barely-pubescent punks started cranking 
the boomin' tunes in a ratty-ass beater bug (prolly had more into
the stereo than I do in my westy) and one of the event staff *RAN* over
and shut him down.  Had to love that!

>It was nice to see so many KG folk at the Kelley Park show...
>
>As one of the people who helps put on the show each year - this was the
>first year in _ten_ that I didn't work the show - I can comment on all
>this. The very short of it is that this is the first year that we have
>actually had to turn anyone away. In years past there weren't any
>water-pumpers - maybe one New-Beetle on display - and they surely
>contributed to the lack of space inside. Also, in years past we were able
>to put overflow on the grass across from the hotel (behind the Ghias).
>This year, somehow they had NOBODY (that I ever saw) parking Ghias, and we
>overflowed it, and normally we'd have overflowed onto the grass behind.
>But there was no room on the grass as some dope-head had permitted the
>setting up of awnings directly behind the cars. Doah! ...It may have also
>been true that they, the city, wouldn't let us park on the grass...
>
>There were quite a few screw ups this year. One was the use of entrance
>gates. In years past the swappers used the north-gate. This time we
>weren't allowed to use it because of the in-experience of the people who
>now manage the park for the city. They were, in short, unwilling to listen
>to us when we told them, "this is how it's been done in years past -
>because it works; please let us do it that way again this year."
>
>Quite a few of us were talking openly at the show of moving it to a new
>location - we've out-grown the location and the citys new Kelley Park
>managers are difficult to deal with, with unreasonable demands borne of
>ignorance. I have proposed, and will at the next meeting will formally
>propose our use of "Farie Land" on the edge of Lake Merrit in Oakland.
>It's got the trees and charm of Kelley Park, and it's much bigger. I've
>already been talking with the city about it as a place for Ghia people to
>hold gatherings... We'll see what they tell us about using it. My bet is
>that they'll be DELIGHTED to "steal" this money-maker from San Jose! And,
>a whole lot of us will like the location a lot better. It'll be cooler,
>closer to services like ATMs and regular resturants - you can easily walk
>to a few dozen resturants for lunch, for example, and it's more centrally
>located for Bay Area people... In fact the ONE reason it might get
>shot-down is that Fearless Leader lives in Gillroy, an hour plus south of 
>K.P. and Farie Land is about an extra 45 minutes to an hour north of
>that... He has been known to discourage and quell anything happening any
>further north than S.J. - and this, from the "Golden Gate" Chapter? Maybe
>they should re-name it the Garlic Gate Chapter!
>
>Oh, while _I'm_ ranting - did anyone else notice the WRONG model name used
>for Karmann Ghia Coupes on the parking signs? They said, "Karmann Ghia
>Sedan". Nope. Sorry. No such animal exists! I have brought this up a few
>times and it has never changed. If I can get a few of you to reply that
>you support the re-making of the sign to read correctly, I could use your
>replies. ...There were some other afronts to Ghia owners too. Anybody
>notice that the car on the t-shirt and artwork wasn't much of a stock
>Ghia? Four lug wheels on a five lug era car, custom bumper, etc. When I
>brought it up, I was told, "oh, I didn't notice - don't know too much
>about Ghias." - this from the pres. of the club. ...Oh, and that's the
>EXACT SAME remark that was made about the mis-printed sign... -sigh-
>
>Please send me all your SPECIFIC feedback on this topic. I plan to
>champion the Ghia cause as best I can at the next meeting.
>
>Regards,
>RT
>
>On Sun, 9 Apr 2000, Tom Mink wrote:
>
>> Date: Sun, 09 Apr 2000 20:26:01 -0700
>> From: Tom Mink <tmink_at_cwo_dot_com>
>> Reply-To: karmannghiaclub_at_lists.tdl_dot_com
>> To: karmannghiaclub_at_lists.tdl_dot_com
>> Subject: [KG] Kelley Park Rant.
>> 
>> Just got back from Kelley Park.  A great show, lots of cars.  The problem?
>> Lots of cars.  I left Sacramento at 5:30am, with a couple of vintage busses
>> (Thomn Fitzpatrick's) tagging along.  Got to KP at about 9:00 to find that
>> the gates were closed to more cars.  *I* could come in, but I had to leave
>> the Ghia outside.  The Ghia that I'd just spent 2 days detailing for this
>> show.  
>> 
>> No sooner than I had parked my car and walked back to the gate than I saw
>> the mighty police and gatekeepers seeing fit to allow a red Ghia coupe in.
>> My inquiries as to why this particular car was allowed in and mine wasn't
>> were not met with much amusement.  
>> 
>> The bottom line to me is this:  This event is BILLED as the "Kelley Park
>> *Vintage* Meet".  Why are stock, vintage cars forced to park outside while
>> assloads of New Beetles, Golfs, Jettas, Superbeetles, and Cal-look Bugs wih
>> "boomin' systems" allowed in?  
>> 
>> Something needs to change, VVWCOA, and soon.
>> 
>> Tom Mink
>> '66 cabrio (No boomin stereo, no radiator, stock height, in other words,
>> vintage).</pre>


